🔧 Key Concepts in Spring Security Config

| Concept               | Description                                                           |
| --------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `SecurityFilterChain` | Core bean that defines security filter rules                          |
| `HttpSecurity`        | Fluent API to configure web-based security for specific http requests |
| `UserDetailsService`  | Provides user details (from memory, DB, etc.)                         |
| `PasswordEncoder`     | Encodes passwords (e.g. BCryptPasswordEncoder)                        |
| `@EnableWebSecurity`  | Enables Spring Security filters                                       |
| `permitAll()`         | Allows access to a specific endpoint without authentication           |
| `authenticated()`     | Requires the user to be authenticated                                 |



✅ Full Example with All Concepts
🔐 1. @EnableWebSecurity + Configuration Class

@Configuration
@EnableWebSecurity
public class SecurityConfig {

    // 🔒 2. Define the SecurityFilterChain
    @Bean
    public SecurityFilterChain securityFilterChain(HttpSecurity http) throws Exception {
        http
            .authorizeHttpRequests(auth -> auth
                .requestMatchers("/public").permitAll()         // 6. permitAll()
                .requestMatchers("/private").authenticated()    // 7. authenticated()
            )
            .formLogin(withDefaults()); // built-in login form

        return http.build();  // 1. SecurityFilterChain bean
    }

    // 🧑‍💻 3. In-memory user store
    @Bean
    public UserDetailsService userDetailsService() {
        UserDetails user = User.builder()
            .username("john")
            .password(passwordEncoder().encode("password"))
            .roles("USER")
            .build();

        return new InMemoryUserDetailsManager(user);  // 3. UserDetailsService
    }

    // 🔐 4. Password encoder
    @Bean
    public PasswordEncoder passwordEncoder() {
        return new BCryptPasswordEncoder();  // 4. PasswordEncoder
    }
}
@RestController
public class MyController {

    @GetMapping("/public")
    public String publicEndpoint() {
        return "This is a public endpoint - no login required!";
    }

    @GetMapping("/private")
    public String privateEndpoint() {
        return "This is a private endpoint - login required!";
    }
}
